Interface BindableColumn<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - - the Java type that corresponds to this column
    All Superinterfaces:
    BasicColumn
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractCount, AbstractTypeConvertingFunction, AbstractUniTypeFunction, Add, Avg, Concatenate, Constant, Count, CountAll, CountDistinct, DerivedColumn, Divide, Lower, Max, Min, Multiply, OperatorFunction, SqlColumn, StringConstant, Substring, Subtract, Sum, Upper
    public interface BindableColumn<T>
extends BasicColumn
    Describes additional attributes of columns that are necessary for binding the column as a JDBC parameter. Columns in where clauses are typically bound.
    Author:
    Jeff Butler
